history.content: Hey I'm in 126 right now. The first part of the class was really difficult for me, as it was pretty much just a much harder version of CS70 probability, but it is starting to get more manageable as we start doing some newer concepts.You should be fine taking it with just CS70, but be willing to put in a lot of work into this class. I'm also involved in ML research, and I'd definitely say 126 is a must, which you should at least take concurrently, but I don't think you have to rush into taking 189, just take it when you feel like you are ready.

How difficult are these classes exactly? How would eecs 126 go with cs 70 and high school math contest background? What about eecs 127 with just math 54? Also, how much more is there to gain from cs 189 by taking 126/127 first? I want to do research in ML/AI topics, so I want to take 189 sooner rather than later, but is taking 189 sophomore fall/spring rushing it too much?
history.subject: eecs 126/127
